The `PricingSection` component displays a set of pricing tiers for a product or service. It's designed to be visually appealing and informative, helping users understand different plan options.

## Purpose

To present different pricing plans in a clear and structured manner, enabling users to compare features and costs. The component includes a "most popular" highlight for a specific tier.

## Key Exports and Functions

*   **`PricingSection()`**: The main component that renders the entire pricing section, including a header and a grid of pricing cards.
*   **`PricingCard({ tier }: PricingCardProps)`**: A sub-component that renders an individual pricing tier card. It displays the tier's name, price, description, features, and a call-to-action button.
*   **`PricingTier` interface**: Defines the structure of a pricing tier object, including `name`, `price`, `period`, `description`, `features`, `cta`, and an optional `highlighted` flag.

## Usage Example

```typescript
import { PricingSection } from '@/components/ui/pricing-section';

function MyPage() {
  return (
    <div>
      {/* Other page content */}
      <PricingSection />
      {/* More page content */}
    </div>
  );
}
```

The `PricingSection` component can be imported and used within any React component to display the pricing information.
